{
  "texts": [
    "The output from both models is concatenated and fed into two dense layers, which perform binary classification using the Softmax activation function.",
    "Using two pretrained models with different architectures allows the hybrid model to capture a broader range of features and improve the accuracy of breast cancer classification.",
    "In our study, we employed the Adam optimizer with adaptive learning rate and decay to enhance the training process of our deep learning model.",
    "The Adam optimizer is well-known for its effectiveness in handling non-stationary and sparse gradients, making it suitable for a wide range of tasks, including image classification.",
    "By utilizing adaptive learning rates, the optimizer dynamically adjusts the learning rate for each parameter during training, which helps improve convergence and accelerates the learning process."
  ]
}